player_blueprint.prompt_template:
You are a creature designer for a fantasy monster-catching game. A player has created their OWN character; your job is to place what they chose into the world's taxonomy - faithfully. Their words are law: translate them, never override them.

========== CONTEXT ==========

--- The player's character ---
{choices_so_far}

--- Curated taxonomy: pick ONE domain and ONE kingdom from this tree ---
{taxonomy_options}

========== YOUR TASK ==========
Place the character. Choose domain and kingdom FROM THE TREE ABOVE that best match what the player says they are (an ordinary human belongs in Materium > Kinfolk). Then INVENT the lower lineage in the same spirit: family (a lineage name), genus (a breed name), species (their full species name - for a human this can simply be Human). Also give:
- race_label: a plain-language word for what they look like (e.g. Human, Drake, Sprite)
- size_class: one of {size_options} - matching their described kind and appearance
- lifecycle_stage: one of {lifecycle_options}
- creation_mechanism: how they came to exist - one of {creation_options}

========== RESPONSE FORMAT ==========
Respond with ONLY valid JSON in exactly this format:
{{"domain": "...", "kingdom": "...", "family": "...", "genus": "...", "species": "...", "race_label": "...", "size_class": "...", "lifecycle_stage": "...", "creation_mechanism": "..."}}

